WEBVTT

00:03.269 --> 00:04.436
<i>"Last Man Standing"</i>
<i>is recorded</i>

00:04.438 --> 00:05.938
<i>In front of a live</i>
<i>studio audience.</i>

00:05.940 --> 00:06.939
[ alarm beeps ]

00:06.941 --> 00:08.607
What did I do?

00:08.609 --> 00:10.709
Oh, that's the new security
system chuck larabee installed.

00:10.711 --> 00:13.112
Just punch 6-2-2-6-2.

00:13.114 --> 00:15.114
It's easy to remember,
it spells "obama."

00:15.116 --> 00:16.782
That's real funny,
honey.

00:16.784 --> 00:18.984
Having obama protect us
from burglars,

00:18.986 --> 00:21.186
Can't even keep putin
out of crimea.

00:22.789 --> 00:25.357
Someone's
got a new benghazi.

00:25.359 --> 00:27.793
Benghazi's
not over yet.
Yeah.

00:27.795 --> 00:29.495
Sweetie,
how was your sleepover?

00:29.497 --> 00:31.063
Awesome.
Grandpa's right.

00:31.065 --> 00:32.698
The house
gets so peaceful

00:32.700 --> 00:34.600
Once all the hens
go to sleep.

00:35.502 --> 00:37.870
What time
did he go to bed?

00:37.872 --> 00:40.539
Earlier than usual.
They moved kimmel to 11:30.

00:40.541 --> 00:43.876
We watched tv
and organized our meat.

00:43.878 --> 00:47.079
Wow, he watches tv
the same way you do.

00:47.081 --> 00:49.648
I'm preparing
our first barbecue.

00:49.650 --> 00:51.717
Burgers, chicken, lamb,
and brisket.

00:51.719 --> 00:53.519
Mmm. Sounds like
the delicious remains

00:53.521 --> 00:56.021
Of a drone strike
on noah's ark.

00:56.023 --> 00:58.190
Uh, what about tofu,
hmm?

00:58.192 --> 00:59.658
I'm sure
mrs. Noah wanted it,

00:59.660 --> 01:01.827
But god said,
"not on this cruise."

01:02.762 --> 01:04.663
Then what is aunt April
gonna eat?

01:04.665 --> 01:07.066
Aunt April?
Is that this weekend?

01:07.068 --> 01:08.734
Yep.
It's on the calendar.

01:08.736 --> 01:11.103
I scratched it out
and put "first barbecue."

01:11.105 --> 01:12.604
Well, that doesn't
make it go away.

01:13.406 --> 01:14.907
I've been talking
to her for a week.

01:14.909 --> 01:16.909
She is really excited
about this visit.
Yeah.

01:16.911 --> 01:18.544
Does she have to come
in the house?

01:18.546 --> 01:19.945
We could just leave
a bag of cash

01:19.947 --> 01:21.413
Out on the front porch.
Oh, honey.

01:21.415 --> 01:23.048
You know, maybe
she's not coming for money.

01:23.050 --> 01:24.349
Maybe she misses me.

01:24.351 --> 01:26.418
If I offered her
400 bucks to visit

01:26.420 --> 01:29.121
Or $410 not to visit,
you know what she'd take.

01:30.190 --> 01:32.691
Uh, I'll leave right now
for $200.

01:32.693 --> 01:34.026
I thought
we were going anyway?

01:34.028 --> 01:36.695
Shh.
Boyd, mommy's working.

01:36.697 --> 01:39.598
Nobody's getting money for
leaving this house until I do,

01:39.600 --> 01:40.999
And then I'm taking half.

01:42.535 --> 01:45.604
-- Captions by vitac --

01:50.710 --> 01:52.911
As I live and breathe.
Chuck larabee.
Hey.

01:52.913 --> 01:55.247
Wow. What are you
doing around here?

01:55.249 --> 01:56.415
Looking
for sleeping bags?

01:56.417 --> 01:58.183
I didn't know you folks
were into camping.

01:59.152 --> 02:02.421
Oh, "we folks" love
to spend time in the woods.

02:02.423 --> 02:05.724
Plotting, planning.
You'll see.

02:05.726 --> 02:08.260
I meant you marines.

02:08.262 --> 02:09.828
You know, I didn't think
you were into camping

02:09.830 --> 02:11.263
After spending all that time
in gulf one.

02:11.265 --> 02:13.432
Oh, I'm sure
that's what you meant.

02:13.434 --> 02:16.335
You turn everything
into a race thing.
Oh.

02:16.337 --> 02:18.971
Makes it almost impossible
to insult you personally.

02:18.973 --> 02:21.273
[ scoffs ]
never stops you from trying.

02:21.275 --> 02:24.143
Hey. You might get more
people of color in this store

02:24.145 --> 02:25.444
If you hired a few.

02:25.446 --> 02:27.179
You know, your employees
look like

02:27.181 --> 02:29.448
The cast of that
"hillbilly handfishin'" show.

02:29.450 --> 02:32.518
You know, we sell
rods and reels here

02:32.520 --> 02:35.754
And don't really like doing
that handfishing idea.

02:35.756 --> 02:38.524
I mean, what's next?
Deer strangling?

02:38.526 --> 02:41.026
If there's a stupid way
to hunt animals,

02:41.028 --> 02:43.529
I'm sure<i> you folks</i>
will get right on it.

02:43.531 --> 02:45.297
What can I help you with?

02:45.299 --> 02:47.099
I'm just
looking at flashlights.

02:47.101 --> 02:50.269
Oh, we've got a great display
down at camping.

02:50.271 --> 02:51.370
Take the hallway down,

02:51.372 --> 02:52.437
Then you'll see
a big, stuffed grizzly bear.

02:52.439 --> 02:53.605
If you see
a real grizzly bear,

02:53.607 --> 02:54.806
You have gone too far.

02:54.808 --> 02:56.175
Huh.

02:57.210 --> 02:58.677
That's your friend chuck?

02:58.679 --> 03:01.647
He's not my friend.
Why do people keep
making that mistake?

03:01.649 --> 03:03.949
Well, 'cause you guys
go back and forth like we do,

03:03.951 --> 03:04.950
And we're friends.

03:04.952 --> 03:05.951
Shut up, kyle.

03:06.853 --> 03:09.054
See? Zing-zang!

03:09.056 --> 03:10.055
I'm glad to see chuck.

03:10.057 --> 03:11.623
I've always wanted
to reach more

03:11.625 --> 03:13.125
Of the african-american
market.

03:13.127 --> 03:15.627
Well, let's not start
with chuck.

03:15.629 --> 03:17.629
If he has a great experience,
maybe he'll tell his friends.

03:17.631 --> 03:20.065
Kyle, I want you
to treat mr. Larabee

03:20.067 --> 03:21.733
Like he owns the store.

03:21.735 --> 03:24.236
You mean give him the friendly
ribbing like I do with you guys?

03:24.238 --> 03:26.238
Shut up, kyle.

03:26.240 --> 03:28.540
How do I keep
walking into that?
That's a good idea, ed.

03:28.542 --> 03:31.176
Yeah, I want you to follow
mr. Larabee around

03:31.178 --> 03:33.912
And treat him like he's
different than everybody else.

03:33.914 --> 03:35.047
Mike: Give him
a lot of attention.
Okay.

03:35.049 --> 03:36.715
[ chuckles ]
oh, wait a minute.

03:36.717 --> 03:38.517
If we give him
too much attention,

03:38.519 --> 03:40.185
He might take it
the wrong way.

03:40.187 --> 03:42.254
Well, if he doesn't,
it won't be funny.

04:21.928 --> 04:23.929
Excuse me.
Can I help you?

04:23.931 --> 04:25.897
No, I'm good.

04:25.899 --> 04:27.399
You finding
everything you need?

04:27.401 --> 04:28.700
I'm fine.

04:28.702 --> 04:30.802
Just so you know,
I know everything in the store,

04:30.804 --> 04:32.804
Where it is,
and how many of them we have.

04:34.474 --> 04:35.607
Good to know.

04:35.609 --> 04:37.576
Can I help you
find anything specific?

04:37.578 --> 04:39.077
Like I said, I'm fine.

04:39.079 --> 04:40.479
Because I wouldn't want you
to spend

04:40.481 --> 04:42.347
Any more time here than you
<i>absolutely</i> have to.

04:44.617 --> 04:46.084
Right.

04:46.086 --> 04:47.219
Do you mind my asking

04:47.221 --> 04:49.288
Why I'm getting
all this special attention?

04:49.290 --> 04:50.689
Not at all, sir.

04:52.091 --> 04:54.793
Why am I getting
all this special attention?

04:54.795 --> 04:56.261
Oh, the top brass said

04:56.263 --> 04:58.563
For me to stay
right on top of you.

04:58.565 --> 05:00.165
It's 'cause you're black.

05:05.838 --> 05:07.839
You know,
mandy baxter fashions

05:07.841 --> 05:09.841
Is not just
about mandy baxter.

05:09.843 --> 05:13.679
It's about helping plain girls
<i>look</i> like mandy baxter.

05:13.681 --> 05:16.682
Honey, plain girls don't really
like being called plain.

05:16.684 --> 05:17.816
I'm sorry, mom.

05:17.818 --> 05:19.885
I keep forgetting
how sensitive you are.

05:22.088 --> 05:25.257
Well, aunt April's here,
and off to a great start.

05:25.259 --> 05:27.926
Parked<i> right</i> in dad's spot.
He's gonna be --

05:27.928 --> 05:30.095
Hi!
[ squeals ]
[ squeals ]

05:30.097 --> 05:31.263
Oh!

05:31.265 --> 05:32.798
Look
at the three of you!

05:32.800 --> 05:35.434
You're like the more beautiful
charlie's angels.

05:35.436 --> 05:37.035
Oooh.
Well, I call farrah.

05:37.037 --> 05:40.205
No, jaclyn smith.
No, cameron diaz.

05:40.207 --> 05:41.606
Which angel am I?

05:41.608 --> 05:42.674
Charlie.

05:44.444 --> 05:46.445
I like it. Smart one
surrounded by bimbos.

05:46.447 --> 05:47.512
Sounds about right.

05:47.514 --> 05:48.647
Oh.
Mm.

05:48.649 --> 05:50.115
Come on in. Sit.

05:50.117 --> 05:51.883
Let's catch up.
How's your life?

05:51.885 --> 05:53.452
You know, pretty great.

05:53.454 --> 05:55.387
Brad and I
are back together.

05:55.389 --> 05:57.122
Mm.
For now.

05:57.124 --> 05:58.890
I haven't checked
my e-mail.

05:58.892 --> 06:00.859
And, uh, what happened

06:00.861 --> 06:02.794
With that clothing store
you opened?

06:02.796 --> 06:04.896
Oh, yeah. The big and tall
shop for women.

06:04.898 --> 06:07.132
Oh, manly gal.

06:08.468 --> 06:11.670
We went out of business.
I lost a bundle.

06:11.672 --> 06:14.806
But I met a<i> ton</i>
of sweet transvestites.

06:16.075 --> 06:17.209
Hey.

06:17.211 --> 06:18.910
Mike!
Hi!

06:18.912 --> 06:20.912
Oh!
[ grunts ]

06:20.914 --> 06:25.517
Ohh! I can't feel
my lower extremities.

06:25.519 --> 06:29.020
How is everyone's
favorite outdoor man?

06:29.022 --> 06:30.789
Well,
wishing he was outdoors.

06:32.091 --> 06:33.492
So, uh, how are you?

06:33.494 --> 06:35.927
Oh, it just feels great
to get out of boulder.

06:35.929 --> 06:37.596
Yeah,
welcome back to america.

06:37.598 --> 06:39.898
Dad, April was just catching us
up on her awesome life.

06:39.900 --> 06:42.100
It's like
a kate hudson rom-com.

06:42.102 --> 06:44.836
Ohh, I should take this call
in the den.

06:44.838 --> 06:46.271
Hey,
your phone didn't ring.

06:46.273 --> 06:47.639
Just let me go.

06:51.077 --> 06:52.844
Well, April,
good to see you here.

06:52.846 --> 06:54.980
If I don't see you again,
have a nice trip.

06:55.948 --> 06:58.917
You're funny.
You'll see me again.

06:58.919 --> 07:01.853
Oh, I don't know.
I-I'm pretty good at this.

07:01.855 --> 07:04.222
Come on.
I got some wine in the kitchen.

07:04.224 --> 07:06.892
Oh, um, I might have done some
cooking with that last night.

07:06.894 --> 07:08.660
[ knock on door ]

07:11.564 --> 07:13.298
Hey, larabee.
Come on in.

07:13.300 --> 07:15.434
Very funny, baxter.

07:15.436 --> 07:18.236
Having a salesman follow me
through the store.

07:18.238 --> 07:21.339
Profiling humor --
not cool.

07:22.942 --> 07:24.643
Yeah,
so, I don't get it.

07:24.645 --> 07:27.245
If a taxi won't pick you up,
you're pissed.
Mm.

07:27.247 --> 07:30.081
If you get too much attention
in my store, you're pissed.

07:30.083 --> 07:32.617
You know what? I think
you just like being pissed.

07:32.619 --> 07:35.754
If you lived in my skin,
you'd understand.

07:35.756 --> 07:38.356
If I lived in your skin,
it'd be kind of baggy on me.

07:40.593 --> 07:44.329
I know at least one part of me
you'd be swimming in.

07:46.632 --> 07:49.267
So, what's up next
for my gorgeous kid sister?

07:49.269 --> 07:51.436
I've kind of hit
a point in my life

07:51.438 --> 07:53.505
Where I want
to get more grounded.

07:53.507 --> 07:55.640
You know,
commit to something real.

07:55.642 --> 07:57.742
Ah. April, I'm glad to hear it.
Good for you.

07:57.744 --> 07:59.711
So I'm gonna have a baby.

08:02.482 --> 08:03.915
What?!

08:03.917 --> 08:06.084
A baby?

08:06.086 --> 08:08.220
Like, on purpose?

08:09.355 --> 08:10.355
You're pregnant?

08:10.357 --> 08:11.423
Oh, heck no.

08:11.425 --> 08:13.959
Apparently
that window is closed.

08:13.961 --> 08:16.528
Slammed shut
right on my uterus.

08:17.430 --> 08:18.997
But that doesn't
make any sense.

08:18.999 --> 08:20.632
You're so beautiful.

08:20.634 --> 08:23.435
Mandy, not a factor.

08:23.437 --> 08:25.670
I'm not gonna
let that stop me.

08:25.672 --> 08:28.773
See, I can buy a donor egg
for like 6 grand,

08:28.775 --> 08:33.111
Which I don't
<i>totally</i> have, so...

08:33.113 --> 08:36.114
Y-you know, I think
there might be a bag of cash

08:36.116 --> 08:37.883
For you
on the front porch.

08:45.558 --> 08:47.359
April having a baby

08:47.361 --> 08:49.227
Is the<i> stupidest</i> idea
I've ever heard.

08:49.229 --> 08:51.196
Shh!
She's in kristin's room.

08:51.198 --> 08:52.230
Oh, I forgot.

08:52.232 --> 08:55.867
Stupidest idea
I've<i> ever</i> heard!

08:55.869 --> 08:57.202
You know,
when we started a family,

08:57.204 --> 08:58.403
We didn't
have all the answers.

08:58.405 --> 08:59.571
When we started a family,

08:59.573 --> 09:01.573
It didn't involve a syringe
and a petri dish.

09:01.575 --> 09:03.675
You know, we had
some of the answers.

09:03.677 --> 09:06.244
No, I had the answers
and you just copied off of me.

09:06.246 --> 09:07.512
April is 40.

09:07.514 --> 09:09.381
Honey, this could be
her last shot.

09:09.383 --> 09:10.415
That's right.

09:10.417 --> 09:12.484
Society almost made
a clean getaway.

09:12.486 --> 09:14.419
Listen,
if she had that kid,

09:14.421 --> 09:16.421
We'd have
to take care of it,

09:16.423 --> 09:18.757
Unless brad and angelina
wanted it.

09:18.759 --> 09:21.660
Yeah. No, I know.
You might be right.

09:21.662 --> 09:23.261
Oh, I'm right.
Gosh.

09:23.263 --> 09:25.597
I guess not everybody's
cut out to be mommies.

09:25.599 --> 09:27.332
I just want
to give my kid sister

09:27.334 --> 09:29.267
The benefit
of the doubt.

09:29.269 --> 09:31.603
That's what we could call our
annual fundraiser for her --

09:31.605 --> 09:33.004
"the benefit of the doubt."

09:37.343 --> 09:39.377
I feel so lucky
having kyle.

09:39.379 --> 09:41.746
Oh, kyle's the one
who's lucky.

09:41.748 --> 09:45.250
In every young man's life,
there is a mandy baxter.

09:45.252 --> 09:47.152
It's usually
mandy baxter.

09:50.389 --> 09:52.791
You know what? I feel
really lucky to have brad.

09:52.793 --> 09:54.893
I'm just hoping
that having this baby

09:54.895 --> 09:56.561
Will get him
to settle down.

09:56.563 --> 09:57.729
Yeah, yeah.

09:57.731 --> 09:59.464
If there's one siren call
a man can't resist,

09:59.466 --> 10:01.333
It's a crying baby.

10:02.568 --> 10:04.135
You know,
when I got pregnant,

10:04.137 --> 10:06.905
Ryan disappeared
for three years.

10:06.907 --> 10:08.540
Well, ryan was young.

10:08.542 --> 10:11.109
Brad's more stable.
He's in a band.

10:11.111 --> 10:14.679
Oh, yeah. Rock on.

10:16.048 --> 10:18.717
Brad would be
<i>crazy</i> to leave you.

10:18.719 --> 10:21.987
You are so beautiful,
and you're so talented.

10:21.989 --> 10:23.955
Mandy, honey,
can you give us a sec?

10:23.957 --> 10:24.956
Oh, yeah, sure.

10:24.958 --> 10:26.758
Oh, mandy and I
have no secrets.

10:26.760 --> 10:29.094
Ah, well, considering
your year as a carny,

10:29.096 --> 10:30.161
That's disturbing.

10:31.397 --> 10:33.999
April, um...

10:34.001 --> 10:37.435
Look, mike and I have
always been willing to help you,

10:37.437 --> 10:40.772
But this --
this donor-egg project...

10:40.774 --> 10:43.642
We just don't feel comfortable
underwriting it.

10:43.644 --> 10:45.310
I'm sorry, honey.

10:45.312 --> 10:47.512
If we don't help her, how is
she gonna start a family, mom?

10:47.514 --> 10:49.948
Yeah, I don't have
anywhere else to turn.

10:49.950 --> 10:52.384
Yes, you do.

10:53.986 --> 10:57.489
I mean, I have eggs, right?

10:57.491 --> 10:58.823
I've got lots of them.

10:58.825 --> 11:01.326
Uh [chuckles]
slow down, mandy.

11:01.328 --> 11:03.862
It's not
loaning her a sweater.

11:06.932 --> 11:08.600
Are you sure?

11:08.602 --> 11:11.002
Um...Yes?

11:11.004 --> 11:13.104
[ both giggle ]

11:13.106 --> 11:16.041
Now I know that my baby
will be brilliant and beautiful,

11:16.043 --> 11:19.377
And your little, baby ears are
gonna set off brad's giant ones.

11:20.046 --> 11:22.180
Wait, wait, w-w-wait.
Th-th-this is a big decision.

11:22.182 --> 11:23.448
If it's a boy, trevor.

11:23.450 --> 11:24.382
Tyler.
Terrence.

11:24.384 --> 11:25.316
Deal.
[ gasps ] deal.

11:25.318 --> 11:26.885
I have always
loved that name.

11:26.887 --> 11:29.187
I'm pretty sure it was on
beyoncÃ©'s short list.

11:30.122 --> 11:32.357
I have to go
call kyle about this.

11:34.794 --> 11:36.494
You're not
seriously considering

11:36.496 --> 11:38.163
Taking mandy up
on this offer.

11:38.165 --> 11:40.131
You saw
how happy she was.

11:40.133 --> 11:42.400
I can't take that
away from her.

11:42.402 --> 11:43.702
Yeah.

11:43.704 --> 11:45.370
You know, she's happy

11:45.372 --> 11:47.572
Because, crazy as it seems,
she looks up to you.

11:47.574 --> 11:50.208
Oh,
and<i> why</i> is that crazy?

11:50.210 --> 11:52.577
[ sighs ]
because, April [sighs]

11:52.579 --> 11:55.380
I mean, you're immature and --
and manipulative,

11:55.382 --> 11:58.249
And...Those are not good
qualities for mandy to admire,

11:58.251 --> 12:00.552
And they're not
good qualities for a mom.

12:00.554 --> 12:01.886
Oh, right.

12:01.888 --> 12:03.688
I can't be a great mom

12:03.690 --> 12:05.990
'cause I'm not a boring
grown-up with a house

12:05.992 --> 12:09.160
Or a husband or a job.

12:10.529 --> 12:12.931
Are -- are you even
hearing yourself?

12:12.933 --> 12:16.735
Vanessa, I don't want
<i>all</i> of the things you have.

12:16.737 --> 12:19.037
I just want<i> one</i> of them.

12:19.039 --> 12:20.505
A child.

12:20.507 --> 12:22.907
Okay. You know, April,
I held your hand

12:22.909 --> 12:25.043
When we walked
to the school bus,

12:25.045 --> 12:27.178
And I will never
stop holding it,

12:27.180 --> 12:28.747
But mandy is my child.

12:28.749 --> 12:31.282
And I'm -- I'm not gonna
let you exploit her.

12:32.585 --> 12:33.651
Wow.

12:34.920 --> 12:37.255
Well, at least mandy
has faith

12:37.257 --> 12:40.425
That I am responsible enough
to handle this.

12:40.427 --> 12:41.793
Now, if you'll excuse me,

12:41.795 --> 12:44.462
I need to get back to boulder
before nightfall,

12:44.464 --> 12:46.765
Because I am driving
on the little tire.

12:59.545 --> 13:01.146
[ gun cocks ]

13:01.148 --> 13:03.381
Hey. Mike baxter here
for outdoor man.

13:03.383 --> 13:06.084
All this month,
it's spring turkey season

13:06.086 --> 13:07.752
Here in colorful colorado.

13:07.754 --> 13:09.220
Gobble! Gobble!

13:09.222 --> 13:11.389
Sitting out here
in this pop-up blind

13:11.391 --> 13:14.592
Gives a hunter plenty of time
to think about the big issues.

13:14.594 --> 13:16.227
Like background checks.

13:16.229 --> 13:17.729
Oh, easy, mike.

13:17.731 --> 13:20.331
Everybody's protected
by the second amendment.

13:20.333 --> 13:22.934
No, no, no. I meant background
checks before having a kid.

13:22.936 --> 13:24.602
Now, you don't
want the government

13:24.604 --> 13:27.005
Sticking its big, fat nose
into something like that,

13:27.007 --> 13:29.240
But somebody
should do something

13:29.242 --> 13:31.309
About stupid people
having kids.

13:31.311 --> 13:34.445
Hillary clinton -- gosh, my
favorite woman on the planet --

13:34.447 --> 13:37.949
Likes to say, "it takes
a village to raise a child."

13:37.951 --> 13:39.317
You know,
it really shouldn't.

13:39.319 --> 13:42.987
Satisfying her husband,
that apparently takes a village.

13:42.989 --> 13:45.757
And not
a particularly attractive one.

13:45.759 --> 13:47.959
So, before you decide
to have a kid,

13:47.961 --> 13:49.594
Give yourself
a little background check.

13:49.596 --> 13:52.330
Ask yourself,
"am I shiftless?

13:52.332 --> 13:55.834
Am I a skanky dingbat
who can't hold down a job?"

13:55.836 --> 13:57.168
If your answer's yes,

13:57.170 --> 13:59.704
Do yourself, the kid,
and society a favor

13:59.706 --> 14:01.539
And go hunting instead.

14:01.541 --> 14:04.509
Rather than adding
another turkey to this world,

14:04.511 --> 14:05.610
Try taking one out.

14:05.612 --> 14:06.678
[ turkey gobbles ]

14:08.447 --> 14:10.949
[ gunshot ]

14:10.951 --> 14:12.450
Bye-bye, birdie.

14:12.452 --> 14:16.354
Great. Now I'm craving
turkey<i> and</i> ann-margret.

14:21.460 --> 14:23.394
Hey.
[ sighs ]

14:23.396 --> 14:24.462
Hey.

14:24.464 --> 14:26.064
Where's your sister?

14:26.066 --> 14:27.532
She went back
to boulder.

14:27.534 --> 14:28.900
All right, I win!

14:30.870 --> 14:32.704
No offense, but it's
worth having her here

14:32.706 --> 14:34.172
Because you get
the sweet relief

14:34.174 --> 14:36.241
When she finally
gets out of here.

14:36.243 --> 14:39.644
Everything tastes better.

14:39.646 --> 14:42.914
Mandy offered to give April
one of her eggs.

14:43.816 --> 14:45.116
Ahh.

14:47.486 --> 14:49.654
How's that beer
tasting now?

14:49.656 --> 14:52.290
Like the first of many.

14:53.826 --> 14:55.493
Did you talk to her?

14:55.495 --> 14:57.262
Well, I was waiting
for you to come home

14:57.264 --> 14:58.930
So we can come up
with a...
Mandy!

14:58.932 --> 15:01.599
...Unified strategy.

15:01.601 --> 15:02.901
What?

15:02.903 --> 15:03.935
This is nuts.

15:03.937 --> 15:05.270
Unless you're
a socialist farmer,

15:05.272 --> 15:07.472
You don't give away
your eggs.

15:08.340 --> 15:09.774
Honey, you offering
to give April

15:09.776 --> 15:11.542
A chance at motherhood
was very generous,

15:11.544 --> 15:13.211
But --
no, you know
what's generous

15:13.213 --> 15:14.612
Is giving back
the panama canal.
Okay.

15:14.614 --> 15:17.048
This --
<i>this</i> is just stupid.

15:17.050 --> 15:20.118
This is like something
jimmy carter would do.

15:20.120 --> 15:22.053
Great. Yes.
Here we go again.

15:22.055 --> 15:25.323
"mandy is<i> so</i> stupid.
She's just like jimmy carter."

15:26.625 --> 15:28.259
Don't I get any credit
for the grades

15:28.261 --> 15:29.894
I've been getting in school?

15:29.896 --> 15:32.096
Or starting
a profitable business?

15:32.098 --> 15:34.699
Or moving the mailbox to
the other side of the driveway

15:34.701 --> 15:37.268
So I wouldn't
keep backing over it?

15:37.270 --> 15:38.970
Honey, you have
grown a lot this year,

15:38.972 --> 15:40.438
And you deserve
a lot of credit,

15:40.440 --> 15:42.040
But not enough
to let you do this.

15:42.042 --> 15:43.775
No way.
Well, I'm sorry,
all right?

15:43.777 --> 15:45.977
What do you mean
you're s--
you guys
can't stop me.

15:45.979 --> 15:48.680
It's my body, my choice,
okay?

15:49.748 --> 15:53.451
College has been
good to you.

15:53.453 --> 15:54.986
She can read
a bumper sticker.

15:54.988 --> 15:56.721
Oh, stop.

16:01.293 --> 16:03.561
So, you had the same exact
argument with your mom

16:03.563 --> 16:04.595
That I did.

16:04.597 --> 16:06.564
I got
the mom-dad tag team.

16:06.566 --> 16:07.565
They were like,
"blah, blah, blah."

16:07.567 --> 16:09.100
And I was like "blah."

16:09.102 --> 16:10.601
I made you a sandwich

16:10.603 --> 16:12.737
'cause I know your egg
is eating for two now.

16:14.239 --> 16:15.239
It's egg salad.

16:15.241 --> 16:16.741
I hope
that's not insensitive.

16:16.743 --> 16:18.142
No, it's okay.

16:18.144 --> 16:19.577
Um, hey, April,

16:19.579 --> 16:21.446
I've been doing
a lot of research.

16:21.448 --> 16:23.781
This whole process is,
like, pretty involved.

16:23.783 --> 16:27.018
Oh, I'm stressed out
even<i> thinking</i> about it.
Yeah.

16:27.020 --> 16:29.454
If I started
the fertility shots in may,

16:29.456 --> 16:31.489
Then they
could do the extraction

16:31.491 --> 16:33.624
And then brad
could add his, um...

16:33.626 --> 16:35.526
Uh -- pbht! --
Ingredient,

16:35.528 --> 16:38.296
And then we're, like,

16:38.298 --> 16:40.264
Pretty much good to go
end of June.

16:40.266 --> 16:41.933
Aah! Nope.

16:43.268 --> 16:45.269
End of June
doesn't work for me.

16:45.271 --> 16:47.105
No, I can't be pregnant

16:47.107 --> 16:49.874
If arcade fire
comes to red rocks.

16:51.276 --> 16:53.177
If win butler
calls me up on stage,

16:53.179 --> 16:54.545
I don't want to be puffy.

16:56.281 --> 16:57.281
Oh, yeah, sure.

16:57.283 --> 16:58.783
Well, when<i> would</i>
work for you?

16:58.785 --> 17:00.885
Uh...Maybe August?

17:00.887 --> 17:03.154
Oh, you know, we're thinking
about going to greece.

17:03.156 --> 17:05.456
Oh, you're
going to greece?

17:05.458 --> 17:09.127
"grease."
I love that musical.

17:09.129 --> 17:10.795
I played kenickie
in high school.

17:10.797 --> 17:12.830
I was not good.

17:12.832 --> 17:14.899
But if you're having a kid,
don't you think,

17:14.901 --> 17:16.901
You know, you should kind of
be saving...?

17:16.903 --> 17:19.337
Ohh, you're right.
You're right.

17:19.339 --> 17:23.141
I mean, this whole thing
is just becoming a whole thing.

17:23.143 --> 17:24.409
Um...

17:24.411 --> 17:26.177
You know,
how about we do September?

17:26.179 --> 17:28.246
Nah, you're gonna be
back in school by then.

17:28.248 --> 17:30.681
Right. And plus, I'll be
starting my new fall line.

17:30.683 --> 17:33.818
Aww, listen to you.
So industrious.

17:33.820 --> 17:36.354
Must make rompers.
Must make rompers.

17:36.356 --> 17:39.090
You know what?
We'll figure it out.

17:39.092 --> 17:40.224
We have time.

17:40.226 --> 17:42.627
It's not like my ovaries
can get any deader.

17:43.562 --> 17:45.096
Okay, well,
we'll talk soon.

17:45.098 --> 17:46.831
Aww, ciao for now.

17:48.267 --> 17:49.600
[ sighs ]

17:49.602 --> 17:51.169
Why are you staring
like that?

17:51.171 --> 17:52.570
You look like
the audience

17:52.572 --> 17:54.338
Through my performance
in "grease."

17:59.111 --> 18:01.379
Um...

18:01.381 --> 18:02.747
Kyle,
I'm just wondering,

18:02.749 --> 18:06.150
Do you think this whole thing
with April is a mistake?

18:08.854 --> 18:12.090
Mandy, I just want you to know
that I support you 100%.

18:12.092 --> 18:14.292
And yes,
it's a horrible mistake.

18:15.627 --> 18:17.128
Really?

18:17.130 --> 18:19.397
Yeah.
Children are precious.

18:19.399 --> 18:21.065
If somebody
wants to have a baby,

18:21.067 --> 18:23.201
They should be serious
and willing to put up

18:23.203 --> 18:25.570
With a little
inconvenience.

18:25.572 --> 18:28.206
That's what I'd want
for any kid that's part yours.

18:28.208 --> 18:30.074
You know, if I was gonna
have a baby,

18:30.076 --> 18:32.043
I'd want it to be
with someone like you.

18:32.045 --> 18:33.211
Deal.

18:33.213 --> 18:34.812
[ gasps ] oh, my god.

18:34.814 --> 18:37.548
I've always
loved that name, too.

18:45.757 --> 18:47.792
[ alarm blares ]
ah! What do I press?

18:47.794 --> 18:49.660
It's
your father's birthday.

18:49.662 --> 18:52.163
Shoot, I didn't
get him anything!

18:52.165 --> 18:54.432
We changed the code
to your father's birthday.

18:54.434 --> 18:56.901
Ladies, ladies, ladies,
it's my birthday.

18:56.903 --> 18:58.603
I know, I forgot.
I'm sorry.

18:58.605 --> 19:00.338
Honey, uh,
the security's --
whoa. Whoa. Whoa.

19:00.340 --> 19:01.806
The light keeps blinking.
I got it. I got it.

19:01.808 --> 19:02.807
I don't know.
Hold it. Hold it.
Hold it.

19:02.809 --> 19:04.108
It's because...

19:04.110 --> 19:06.244
One of the window sensors
is out.

19:06.246 --> 19:07.612
I got to go look at that.

19:07.614 --> 19:08.613
Hey.
Hi.

19:08.615 --> 19:09.647
Everything okay?

19:09.649 --> 19:10.648
Yes.

19:10.650 --> 19:12.150
Um...

19:12.152 --> 19:14.785
I told aunt April that
I couldn't give her an egg.
Ah.

19:14.787 --> 19:15.920
My choice.

19:15.922 --> 19:18.456
Okay. Good.
I think it's the right choice.

19:18.458 --> 19:20.124
Right.
I'm proud of you.
Yeah.

19:20.126 --> 19:21.759
You're no jimmy carter.

19:23.929 --> 19:24.929
I'm gonna go to bed.

19:24.931 --> 19:26.531
Got some rompers
to sew tomorrow.

19:26.533 --> 19:27.532
Mwah!
Oh, good.

19:27.534 --> 19:30.635
Night, dad.
Happy birthday.

19:30.637 --> 19:32.270
I'm proud of you.

19:32.272 --> 19:33.971
Have a good night.

19:33.973 --> 19:36.974
She has turned into a really
ambitious young woman.

19:36.976 --> 19:38.776
Somebody did
a good job parenting.

19:38.778 --> 19:40.111
You're welcome.

19:40.113 --> 19:41.379
Listen...

19:41.381 --> 19:43.147
I got to fix this window

19:43.149 --> 19:45.116
And then I'll be up
for my birthday present.

19:45.118 --> 19:47.618
So, uh, brace yourself.

19:56.461 --> 19:58.663
Okay,
hold it right there.

19:58.665 --> 19:59.897
Keep your hands
where I can see them.

19:59.899 --> 20:01.465
Hey.
It's just a false alarm.

20:01.467 --> 20:04.368
One of my screen sensors
looks like it came loose.

20:04.370 --> 20:06.637
I'm gonna need to see
some I.D.

20:06.639 --> 20:08.439
I don't have any I.D.
I live here.

20:09.474 --> 20:11.142
This house.
Look at my desk.

20:11.144 --> 20:12.677
You'll see a picture of me
sitting right on that desk.

20:12.679 --> 20:13.711
Look at that.

20:13.713 --> 20:16.080
So you've been
looking in the windows?

20:16.082 --> 20:17.748
What's going on, hal?

20:17.750 --> 20:20.051
Responding to an alarm,
mr. Larabee.
Uh-huh.

20:20.053 --> 20:22.920
Found this one
by the front window.

20:23.922 --> 20:27.358
Yeah, he does fit the profile
of a peeping tom --

20:27.360 --> 20:32.430
Middle-aged,
sweatpants, peeping.

20:32.432 --> 20:33.831
He says
he's the resident.

20:33.833 --> 20:37.602
Mm. Straight out of
the peeping-tom handbook.

20:37.604 --> 20:40.004
This is real funny,
larabee.
[ chuckles ]

20:40.006 --> 20:41.872
You know, I could
put this on yelp.

20:41.874 --> 20:44.408
[ chuckles ] I'll vouch for him,
hal. Go ahead, guys.

20:44.410 --> 20:46.777
Okay.
Take it easy, boss.
See?

20:46.779 --> 20:48.412
Hey, doesn't feel so good,
does it?

20:48.414 --> 20:50.214
You know --
when people jump
to conclusions about you?

20:50.216 --> 20:51.582
You know
what doesn't feel good

20:51.584 --> 20:54.418
Is hiring an incompetent
security company.

20:54.420 --> 20:56.420
You know, that window sensor's
loose or something.

20:56.422 --> 20:57.922
Keeps showing up
on this alarm pad.

20:57.924 --> 20:59.790
Oh, you probably
changed the pass code

20:59.792 --> 21:01.425
Without resetting
the system.

21:01.427 --> 21:02.994
Did you switch out obama?

21:03.929 --> 21:05.896
It was a change
I could believe in.

21:05.898 --> 21:07.732
Yeah. [ chuckles ]

21:07.734 --> 21:09.867
Oh, yeah, it's been
a tough five years.

21:09.869 --> 21:13.070
Bin laden's dead
and the stock market's doubled.

21:13.072 --> 21:14.905
Hang in there.

21:14.907 --> 21:17.475
Yeah. No doubt,
things have gotten better.
Mm.

21:17.477 --> 21:20.645
Bush's policies
have finally kicked in.

21:20.647 --> 21:22.280
[ laughs ]

21:22.282 --> 21:24.282
Good night, baxter.

21:24.284 --> 21:26.951
Night, larabee.
